Reasoning: The paper deals with the design of lossless distributed source codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of Reed-Solomon codes and LDPC codes also falls under the category of coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the performance of the codes under different correlation structures, which is related to the study of random processes and statistical inference (cs.DS, cs.SI). Finally, the simulations involve multimedia data compression (cs.MM).
